TSC2007 kernel module setup:
Before compiling, install the kernel source

Prep - on the target RasPi:
    1) sudo raspi-config
    2) expand_rootfs
    3) boot_behavior -> Yes
    4) sudo apt-get update
    5) sudo apt-get upgrade
    6) sudo apt-get install libi2c-dev libx11-dev libxext-dev libxi-dev x11proto-input-dev
    7) sudo reboot

On another machine - obtain the kernel source, tar it, and scp it:
    1) mkdir git
    2) cd git
    3) git clone https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux
    4) git clone https://github.com/raspberrypi/firmware
    5) tar -cvf linux.tar.gz --exclude .git linux
    6) scp linux.tar.gz pi@raspberrypi:/home/pi

On the RasPi:
    1) tar -xvf linux.tar.gz
    2) cd linux
    3) zcat /proc/config.gz > .config
    4) make oldconfig
    5) make modules_prepare

On the other machine:
    1) scp firmware/extra/Module.symvers pi@raspberrypi:/home/pi/linux

On the RasPi:
    1) sudo mkdir /usr/src/kernels
    2) sudo mv linux /usr/src/kernels/$(uname -r)
    3) cd /lib/modules/$(uname -r)
    4) sudo ln -s /usr/src/kernels/$(uname -r) build
    5) sudo ln -s /usr/src/kernels/$(uname -r) source


Building and installation is on the Pi

Compile and install the tsc2007 module:
    1) cd tsc2007
    2) make
    3) sudo make install
    4) sudo modprobe tsc_raspi
    5) sudo modprobe tsc2007

To calibrate:

Compile and run xinput_calibrator:
    1) Obtain xinput_calibrator-*.tar.gz from www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/xinput_calibrator
    2) tar -xvf xinput_calibrator-*.tar.gz
    3) cd xinput_calibrator-*
    4) ./configure
    5) make
    6) src/xinput_calibrator
    7) Follow the instructions, i.e.
    8) sudo mkdir /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d
    9) sudo nano /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/99-calibration.conf
